===============================================================================

Sources
-------

 * Banshee 0.11.6 Tarball:
   http://banshee-project.org/files/banshee/banshee-0.11.6.tar.bz2
   http://banshee-project.org/files/banshee/banshee-0.11.6.tar.gz
 
 * ipod-sharp 0.6.2 Tarball:
   http://banshee-project.org/files/ipod-sharp/ipod-sharp-0.6.2.tar.gz

 * libipoddevice 0.5.2 Tarball:
   http://banshee-project.org/files/libipoddevice/libipoddevice-0.5.2.tar.gz

 * njb-sharp 0.3.0 Tarball:
   http://banshee-project.org/files/njb-sharp/njb-sharp-0.3.0.tar.gz

ChangeLogs
----------
 
 * http://banshee-project.org/files/banshee/banshee-0.11.6.changes

Dependencies
------------

 * Mono 1.1.10 and full stack
 * gtk-sharp-2.0 2.8 or 2.10
 * GStreamer 0.10.3 
 * sqlite3
 * libmusicbrainz 2.1.1 or better
 * libnautilus-burn 2.12 or better
 * GTK+ 2.8 or better
 * HAL 0.5.2 or better (0.5.6+ Recommended)


===============================================================================
MAJOR FEATURE/FIXES/PERFORMANCE UPDATES
===============================================================================

Cool New Features
-----------------

 * Radio stations can now be added/edited/removed from the radio plugin; 
   additionally the remote stations can be easily and optionally disabled 

 * Usability and interface updates to the podcast plugin

 * Audio profiles can now be translated; a number of UI improvements and
   simplifications were made to the profiles as well

 * Updated the volume button to behave like Totem/GNOME's (Bacon)

 * New Slovenian translation by Matej Urbančič

 * Updated translations: Czech (Jakub Friedl), Norwegian bokmål (Kjartan 
   Maraas), Polish (Artur Flinta), Russian (Alexandre Prokoudine), 
   Swedish (Daniel Nylander)

 * UI style updates for the main interface; more improvements in the 
   track list column headers

 * Updated internal daap-sharp version to fix problems with track numbers
   not showing up (James Willcox)

For all the Awesome Banshee Developers
--------------------------------------

 * With this release (0.11.6), the 0.11.x series is now string frozen

 * Moved to GNOME Subversion

 * Project layout has been almost completely reorganized

 * All of Banshee can now be built and run from MonoDevelop


===============================================================================
BUGZILLA OVERVIEW
===============================================================================

Noteworthy bugs fixes/enhancements embraced in this release
-----------------------------------------------------------

 * 399462 - Fix crash on source properties for DAPs (Aaron Bockover)
 * 398491 - Mass storage DAP should use file name conventions (Gabriel Burt)
 * 399650 - Updated strings for usability in the track editor (Aaron Bockover)
 * 342942 - Improper cover art cropping (Aaron Bockover)

Show all bugs marked FIXED during this release cycle
----------------------------------------------------

 * http://banshee-project.org/files/closedbugs.php/2007-01-22,2007-02-05

File Bugs... Be Proactive... Contribute to Open Source!
-------------------------------------------------------

 * Please do not hesitate to file bugs against Banshee in GNOME Bugzilla.
 * http://bugzilla.gnome.org, component: banshee
 * Discuss Banshee on the mailing list list or in #banshee on irc.gnome.org.
 * Lots of information on the Banshee Wiki: http://banshee-project.org
 * Need to debug Banshee? http://banshee-project.org/Debugging


